(power_internal, power_logic).explanation: Power_logic is a component of power_internal, where logic circuits contribute to the total internal power consumption of the processor;

(power_internal, area_cell_area).explanation: Larger cell area typically leads to higher power consumption due to increased capacitance and longer interconnects, thus area_cell_area influences power_internal;

(power_internal, power_register).explanation: Power_register represents the power consumed by register files and is a component that contributes to the total power_internal of the processor;
